ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How much time did you child spend playing in the yard or street around your house (or the house of a friend, neighbour, or relative), from wake-up until noon?
Notes: 0= 0 min; 1= 1-15 min; 2= 16-30 min; 3= 31-60 min; 4= Over 60 min; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: How much time did you child spend playing in the yard or street around your house (or the house of a friend, neighbour, or relative), from noon until 6 pm?
Notes: 0= 0 min; 1= 1-15 min; 2= 16-30 min; 3= 31-60 min; 4= Over 60 min; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: How much time did you child spend playing in the yard or street around your house (or the house of a friend, neighbour, or relative), from 6 pm until bedtime?

ElementDescription: How much time did your child spend playing at a park, playground, or outdoor recreation area (for example, swimming pool, zoo, or amusement park), including while at school or at preschool, from wake-up until noon?

ElementDescription: How much time did your child spend playing at a park, playground, or outdoor recreation area (for example, swimming pool, zoo, or amusement park), including while at school or at preschool, from noon until 6 pm?

ElementDescription: How much time did your child spend playing at a park, playground, or outdoor recreation area (for example, swimming pool, zoo, or amusement park), including while at school or at preschool, from 6 pm until bedtime?
